edu.stanford.math.plex4.homology.barcodes
Class Interval<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

java.lang.Object
  edu.stanford.math.plex4.homology.barcodes.Interval<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the underlying type - e.g. most likely Integer, Double, or Float
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Interval<T>>
public class Interval<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Interval<T>>, java.io.Serializable

This class implements the functionality of an interval of values of any comparable type. It supports finite, semi-infinite, and infinite intervals with open or closed end points.

Author:
Andrew Tausz
